text.tspan: 5.2SUPPLIER/ SERVICE PROVIDER RISK ASSESSMENTCompany recognizes the Risks associated with procurement and has defined broadly systems to avoid or reduce its impact. Procurement can be divided into 3 Categories:1) Stores2) Spares3) Repair and Maintenance ServicesThe following risk matrix broadly sums up the mentioned categories, risk levels and controls.REPAIR ANDMAINTENANCEPropulsion & PowerGeneration Equipment,Thrusters, NavigationEquipment, GMDSSEquipment & DPSystemsCargo HandlingEquipment, Oily WaterSeparator, SewageTreatment Plant, BallastWater Treatment Plantand IncineratorOther MachinerySUPPLY OF SPARESPropulsion & PowerGeneration Equipment,Thrusters, NavigationEquipment, GMDSSEquipment & DPSystemsCargo HandlingEquipment, Oily WaterSeparator, SewageTreatment Plant, BallastWater Treatment Plantand IncineratorOther MachinerySUPPLY OF STORESTow Wire and Work Wireon AHTs VesselsMedicines, Charts,Mooring Ropes andCrane WiresDeck, Engine andCatering Consumables &Provisions.POTENTIAL FORINCIDENT RISKLEVELCategory A Incidents –High RiskCategory B Incidents –Medium RiskCategory C Incidents –Low RiskCONTROLSClass A Suppliers to beused.Only Class A or BSuppliers to be used.Only Class A, B or CSuppliers to be used.Note: The Incident Categorisation is as per HSEQAM 15.2.5.25.3SUPPLIERS AND CONTRACTORSIn order to meet the owners requirements it is essential that when placing orders for products and services from the Company'ssuppliers / service providers the orders are clear, precisely defined and include any applicable standards so that the ability of thesupplier / service provider to meet these requirements can be confirmed.Suppliers and service providers fall into one of 4 classes:CLASS A: These vendors are either Makers, Original Equipment Manufacturers or their authorized agents / distributors.CLASS B: These are vendors who have been evaluated and included in the approved list.CLASS C: These are vendors who do not one or more criteria for evaluation but may be used for low risk supplies / services.CLASS D: These Vendors are not recommended because of:a. Un-favourable past experienceb. Serious breach of agreementc. Owner’s advice.In case of any deviations from the above, secondary approval is required from General Manager and additional controls shall beinvolved by means of forewarning the vessel that the supplier / service providers is not from our approved list and closer monitoring isrequired by the Chief Engineer or the Master of the products being supplied.Class D – Suppliers / service providers are not to be utilized. Any deviation requires express approval from the Managing Director.Supplies of lubricants, paints, chemicals, welding equipment and gases shall be made through manufacturer of these products or theirauthorized distributors, for which agreements shall be drawn by the Company with the suppliers. Wherever it necessitates contractsto be signed, same shall be done by the General Manager or a person designated by him.5.4EVALUATION AND APPROVAL OF SUPPLIERS AND SUBCONTRACTORSFor inclusion of new companies in the approved list of standard company suppliers they will be required to fill the “TA-03 SupplierService Provider HSEQ Questionnaire”. The supplier shall then be evaluated using the form “TA-01 Supplier / Service ProviderEvaluation” which will be reviewed and approved by the General Manager. Approval will qualify them for the inclusion.Amongst other factors the following shall be taken into consideration:1) Is the vendor / service provider ISO 14001 certified.2) Does the vendor have adequate resources and systems in place to enable us to meet our environmental protection standards.A re-evaluation of all the approved Suppliers and Service Provider is to be carried out once in 4 years, in first month of the year andthe process is similar to that of the initial evaluation and approval. This shall be reported in the 1st Quarter Management Review toconfirm compliance. Evaluation carried out by Executive Ship Management (our sister concern) shall be accepted based on a desktopreview.In order to facilitate this, an approved supplier / service providers list with date of Initial / Periodic Evaluation will be maintained. Thefiling system of the suppliers / service providers also facilitate this by filing in four files namely current year, current year -1, currentyear -2 and current year -3. 5.5SUPPLIER AND SERVICE PROVIDER ASSESSMENT/ RECORDSThe company’s approved suppliers and service providers shall be assessed annually using the form “TA-02 Supplier / Service ProviderAssessment” for their ability to consistently meet the company’s requirements with regard to:
